udpkg
======

mini clone of the debian package management system.



how to use
-----------

udpkg -i	| installs a .deb package.
udpkg -l	| lists currrent installed packages. 
udpkg -r	| removes a package.
udpkg -L	| lists choosen package files.
udpkg -i -f	| forces a .deb package installation, even if deps are missing.
